36
00:01:55,889 --> 00:02:01,406
Choose the right pattern - Cache-aside for reads, write-through for consistency.

37
00:02:01,406 --> 00:02:05,853
Set appropriate TTLs - Balance freshness vs performance.

38
00:02:05,853 --> 00:02:10,721
Use proper data structures - Hashes for objects, sorted sets for rankings.

39
00:02:10,721 --> 00:02:15,661
Implement connection pooling - Essential for high-concurrency applications.

40
00:02:15,661 --> 00:02:20,132
Use pipelines - Reduce network round-trips for bulk operations.

41
00:02:20,132 --> 00:02:25,456
Plan invalidation strategy - Tag-based or version-based for complex scenarios.

42
00:02:25,456 --> 00:02:29,663
Monitor cache hit rates - Aim for 90%+ hit rate.

